ONNX BACKENDS

This crate provides Rust streaming wrappers around three open-source
neural pitch estimation models. The Rust code in this crate is original
and does not include code from any upstream project. **No model weights
are bundled in this crate.** End-users must obtain weights from
upstream and comply with each model's license when redistributing
binaries that bundle or download them.

  • SwiftF0 (Lemonfold)
    — Upstream license: MIT.
    — Recommended source: `lars76/swift-f0` (PyPI wheel).
    — No additional obligations beyond MIT attribution.

  • CREPE (Kim, Salamon, Li, Bello — ICASSP 2018)
    — Upstream license: MIT.
    — Recommended source: `yqzhishen/onnxcrepe` (pre-converted ONNX, MIT).
    — No additional obligations beyond MIT attribution.

  • RMVPE (Wei et al. — Interspeech 2023, arXiv 2306.15412)
    — Upstream code license: Apache-2.0 (Dream-High/RMVPE).
    — Recommended source: `lj1995/VoiceConversionWebUI/rmvpe.onnx` on
      HuggingFace (~362 MB, MIT mirror).
    — Vocal-tuned, robust to polyphonic accompaniment. Permissive
      licensing — no obligations beyond Apache-2.0 / MIT attribution.

  • PESTO (Riou et al. — ISMIR 2023) — gated behind the `pesto` feature
    — Upstream license: **LGPL-3.0**. The pretrained weights have no
      separate license declared upstream and so inherit LGPL-3.0 by
      default. Treat exported PESTO ONNX as LGPL-3.0 derivative when
      redistributing.
    — Source: `SonyCSLParis/pesto` GitHub, `pesto-pitch` PyPI.
    — The `pesto` feature is **off by default** so that pure-MIT/Apache
      consumers don't accidentally pull a backend whose weights carry
      LGPL-3.0 obligations. Enable it explicitly if you intend to use
      PESTO and you are prepared to comply with LGPL-3.0 on the model
      file you distribute.

